ProcessingCheckpoint

Description

Tracked points along the processing of a request. May be used for troubleshooting requests which fail or never complete processing.

Fields
Field Name Description
checkpointType - ProcessingCheckpointType! Whether the checkpoint was reached in the normal processing path or in an error or failure path.
checkpointDateTime - DateTime! Time this checkpoint entry was logged to the database.
Example
{
  "checkpointType": "NORMAL",
  "checkpointDateTime": "2007-12-03T10:15:30Z"
}
Types

ProcessingCheckpointType

Description

Type of a given checkpoint in the processing of a request. Not all request pipelines will utilize all checkpoint types.

Values
Enum Value Description

NORMAL

 Checkpoint is in the normal successful processing path.

ERROR

 Checkpoint is in a path reached after there were validation failures in the data.

FAILURE

 Checkpoint is in a path reached though an unexpected procesing failure.
Example
"NORMAL"
Types

ProcessingResult

Description

Result of the attempt to process the action request in the destination system

Fields
Field Name Description
status - String!
requestDateTime - DateTime!
lastStatusCheckDateTime - DateTime
processedDateTime - DateTime Time the request was noted as completed processing, whether successful or not.
errorMessages - String Any error messages generated during processing.
hasWarnings - Boolean! Whether any warnings were generated during processing.
jobs - [RequestJobResult!] List of the individual destination-system jobs that were required to process this request.
checkpoints - [ProcessingCheckpoint!] Checkpoints reached during the processing of the request. Not all action requests will have checkpoints.
Example
{
  "status": "xyz789",
  "requestDateTime": "2007-12-03T10:15:30Z",
  "lastStatusCheckDateTime": "2007-12-03T10:15:30Z",
  "processedDateTime": "2007-12-03T10:15:30Z",
  "errorMessages": "abc123",
  "hasWarnings": false,
  "jobs": [RequestJobResult],
  "checkpoints": [ProcessingCheckpoint]
}
Types

RequestJobResult

Description

Results of the job as submitted to the ERP system.

Fields
Field Name Description
jobId - String! Identifier of the type of job submitted.
jobStatus - String! Current status of the oracle job.
assignedJobId - String Optional value which the pipeline generates as part of the data file to identify the records that need to be processed. This is the Group ID for GL entries and the Batch Name for PPM Costs. Not all jobs will have a value to place here.
jobReport - String Job report or log output from executing the request on the ERP system.
failedRecords - String Records which caused the job to fail.
completedDateTime - DateTime Time the job completion was recorded.
Example
{
  "jobId": "xyz789",
  "jobStatus": "xyz789",
  "assignedJobId": "xyz789",
  "jobReport": "xyz789",
  "failedRecords": "xyz789",
  "completedDateTime": "2007-12-03T10:15:30Z"
}
Types

RequestJobResultValues

Description

Generated values related to request which have been extracted from the downstream system. This property may not be filled in until some time after the process has completed, as data may have to be retrieved from scheduled data extracts.

Fields
Field Name Description
jobType - String! The identifier of the type of job executed that generated the values. This will be a value like 'gl_journal' or 'ppm_costs'.
values - [RequestResultValue!]! The values extracted from the downstream system for the given job.
Example
{
  "jobType": "abc123",
  "values": [RequestResultValue]
}

RequestResultValue

A single value extracted from the downstream system.

Fields
Field Name Description

value - String! Value extracted from the downstream system.
Example
{
  "name": "abc123",
  "value": "xyz789"
}
Types

RequestResultValues

Description

Values related to request which have been extracted from the downstream system. This property may not be filled in until some time after the process has completed, as data may have to be retrieved from scheduled data extracts.

Fields
Field Name Description
valuesExtracted - Boolean! Whether the Values have yet been extracted from the downstream system.
jobs - [RequestJobResultValues!]! The values extracted from the downstream system.
Example
{
  "valuesExtracted": true,
  "jobs": [RequestJobResultValues]
}
Types

RequestStatus

Description

Status options within the ActionRequestStatus that reflect the states a request can be in.

Values
Enum Value Description

PENDING

 Request has been submitted to the server, but not validated or processed.

INPROCESS

 Request has been picked up for processing.

ERROR

 There was an error processing the request after it was picked up.

PROCESSED

 Request has been processed, but the callback has not been completed.

COMPLETE

 If Callback URL Provided: Request has been processed, and the callback was successfully contacted. Or, request has been processed, and no callback URL was provided.

STALE

 If Callback URL Provided: Request has been processed, but repeated attempts to contact the callback have failed and no more will be tried.

REJECTED

 There was a validation error in the request payload data.
Example
"PENDING"

Types

ScmInvoiceLineInput

Description

Invoice Lines attributes for ScmInvoicePayment.

Fields
Input Field Description
itemDescription - String! The description of the item in the invoice line. The default value is populated from the inventory item.
lineAmount - Float! The line amount in invoice currency. The value must be provided while creating an invoice line.
lineType - ScmLineType! The type of invoice line. The value must be provided while creating an invoice line. The valid values are Item, Freight and Miscellaneous. A list of accepted values is defined in the lookup type INVOICE LINE TYPE and can be reviewed using the Setup and Maintenance work area, and the Manage Payables Lookups task.
purchaseOrderLineNumber - PositiveInt The purchase order line number that is matched to the invoice line.
quantity - PositiveFloat The quantity of items invoiced include matched invoice lines, price corrections, quantity corrections, and unmatched invoice lines.
unitPrice - Float The price charged per unit of a good or service.
glSegments - GlSegmentInput
glSegmentString - GlSegmentString Delimited complete GL segment string. All fields of the GL Accounting Key must be provided.
ppmSegments - PpmSegmentInput PPM POET segment values. If provided, this will override any provided or default GL segments.
ppmSegmentString - PpmSegmentString PPM POET segment values. If provided, this will override any provided or default PPM segments.
Example
{
  "itemDescription": "xyz789",
  "lineAmount": 987.65,
  "lineType": "ITEM",
  "purchaseOrderLineNumber": 123,
  "quantity": 123.45,
  "unitPrice": 123.45,
  "glSegments": GlSegmentInput,
  "glSegmentString": GlSegmentString,
  "ppmSegments": PpmSegmentInput,
  "ppmSegmentString": PpmSegmentString
}

Description

Main payload object for a scmInvoicePaymentCreate operation. See operation documentation for more info.

Fields
Input Field Description
accountingDate - LocalDate The date when the payment is to be accounted.
businessUnit - NonEmptyTrimmedString240! Indicates the business unit name for the invoice.
invoiceDescription - NonEmptyTrimmedString240! The statement that describes the invoice.
invoiceAmount - Float! The invoice amount in transaction currency. The value must be provided while creating an invoice.
invoiceDate - LocalDate The date on the supplier invoice. The value can either be provided while creating an invoice or populated by default to the system date.
invoiceType - ScmInvoiceType! The type of the invoice. The valid invoice types are Standard, Prepayment, Credit Memo, Debit Memo.
invoiceLines - [ScmInvoiceLineInput!]! The payables invoice lines resource is used to manage details about goods and services, which includes freight, and miscellaneous charges that can be allocated to item lines.

ScmSupplier

Description

A defined supplier of goods or services in the ERP system.

Each supplier may have multiple sites at which they do business. It is necessary to identify both the supplier and site when submitting a payment.

Supplier in Oracle replaces Vendor in KFS.

endDateActive - LocalDate The date till which the value is available for use.
lastUpdateDateTime - DateTime! Timestamp this record was last updated in the financial system.
lastUpdateUserId - ErpUserId User ID of the person who last updated this record.
sites - [ScmSupplierSite!]! Supplier business locations referenced when making orders or payments to the supplier.
Example
{
  "supplierId": {},
  "startDateActive": "2020-07-19",
  "endDateActive": "2020-07-19",
  "lastUpdateDateTime": "2007-12-03T10:15:30Z",

SearchCommonInputs

Description

Special properties common to all common search operations.

Fields
Input Field Description
sort - [String!] Array of property names to sort on
limit - PositiveInt maximum number of records to retrieve
startIndex - NonNegativeInt Record number to start with
includeTotalResultCount - Boolean Whether to include a count of all records to be returned by this search. Will increase search time.
Example
{
  "sort": ["abc123"],
  "limit": 123,
  "startIndex": 123,
  "includeTotalResultCount": false
}
Types

SearchResultMetadata

Description

Metadata about the search results returned in a given response. Used to provide metrics of the results and the information necessary to pull in the next set of records.

Fields
Field Name Description
sort - [String!] Array of property names used to sort the results
limit - PositiveInt requested limit to the number of records to retrieve
returnedResultCount - NonNegativeInt! Results returned in the data property.
startIndex - NonNegativeInt! Starting index for the current result set.
nextStartIndex - NonNegativeInt Start index for getting the next page of results. Unset if there are no more results.
totalResultCount - NonNegativeInt Total number of results. Will only be populated if includeTotalResultCount is true in the search request.
Example
{
  "sort": ["xyz789"],
  "limit": 123,
  "returnedResultCount": 123,
  "startIndex": 123,
  "nextStartIndex": 123,
  "totalResultCount": 123
}

Types

StringFilterInput

Description

String filter criteria object, only one of this object's properties should be set. Except as noted in the properties below, all comparisons are case-sensitive.

Fields
Input Field Description
eq - String Test if property is equal to the given value
ne - String Test if property is NOT equal to the given value
le - String Test if property is less than or equal to the given value
lt - String Test if property is less than the given value
ge - String Test if property is greater than or equal to the given value
gt - String Test if property is greater than the given value
beginsWith - String Test if property begins with the given value. Case-insensitive.
endsWith - String Test if property ends with the given value. Case-insensitive.
contains - String Test if property contains the given value. Case-insensitive.
notContains - String Test if property does not contain the given value. Case-insensitive.
between - [String!] Test if property is between the first 2 elements in the array
in - [String] Test if property is equal to one of the given values
Example
{
  "eq": "abc123",
  "ne": "xyz789",
  "le": "xyz789",
  "lt": "xyz789",
  "ge": "xyz789",
  "gt": "abc123",
  "beginsWith": "xyz789",
  "endsWith": "xyz789",
  "contains": "abc123",
  "notContains": "xyz789",
  "between": ["xyz789"],
  "in": ["xyz789"]
}

Types

ValidationResponse

Description

Contains the validation overall status and any error messages and the properties they belong to.

Fields
Field Name Description
valid - Boolean! Whether the overall validation succeeded or failed.
errorMessages - [String!] Array of all errors found during validation. The failed property is in the matching index in the messageProperties list.
messageProperties - [String!] Property names which failed validation. May be blank if the validation applies to the entire payload or no particular property.
Example
{
  "valid": false,
  "errorMessages": ["xyz789"],
  "messageProperties": ["abc123"]
}
